  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Your repeated encounters with a particular type of enemy have honed your skills against that foe.</em><br /><br /><strong>Prerequisites</strong><br />No levels in a class that has the favored enemy class feature.<br /><br /><strong>Benefits</strong><br />When you select this feat, choose a specific kind of creature, such as wolf, frost giant, goblin, or babau demon. You gain the ranger's favored enemy class ability against this particular type of creature with a bonus of +2. This feat does not grant the favored enemy class feature for the purposes of prerequisites. If you later gain the favored enemy class feature, you can replace this feat with a feat for which you qualify and whose prerequisites include the favored enemy class feature.<br /><br /><strong>Special</strong><br />You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a different creature.</p>\n<p><br /><strong>Pathfinder Society<br /></strong>'Human' is not a legal choice for the Dedicated Adversary feat, but a human ethnicity such as 'Ulfen' is legal</p>",
